The South African Football Association (SAFA) have suspended Bafana Bafana coach Ephraim Shakes Mashaba after a regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday. Safa did not divulge what happened at the stadium. The federation said Mashaba will not go with Bafana to Mozambique when they take on the Os Mambas in a friendly match on Tuesday. Assistant Coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the team. A statement from SAFA reads: Bafana Bafana Head Coach Ephraim Shakes Mashaba will not join the team on their trip to Mozambique as the Association has deemed it necessary to employ disciplinary measures after a regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday, 12 November 2016. Assistant Coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the team in the above-mentioned international friendly match against Mozambique on Tuesday, 15 November 2016 in Maputo. As is our custom in matters such as these, the Association will not be making any further comments on this matter out of respect for the dignity of the Head Coach and the Association and the legally privileged nature of such proceedings. 